[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-       [0m[35m/[0m[39m* If this is the MakerNote, remember the offset *[0m[35m/[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-       [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->tag == EXIF_TAG_MAKER_NOTE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-       [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->size > [0m[1;36m6[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-       [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m       entry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, entry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, [0m     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-       [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m       entry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m6[0m[1;39m][0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                           size_t size, size_t offset[0m[1;39m)[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    size_t unit, s, data_offset;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Header guard: prevent wrap and ensure [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m-byte header fits *[0m[35m/[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset > SIZE_MAX - [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m || offset + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        exif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                  [0m[32m"Entry header overruns buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%zu + 12 > %zu[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m,[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                  offset, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    entry->tag        = exif_get_short [0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    entry->format     = exif_get_short [0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    entry->components = exif_get_long  [0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Logging entry load *[0m[35m/[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    exif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+              [0m[32m"Loading entry 0x%x [0m[32m([0m[32m'%s'[0m[32m)[0m[32m..."[0m[39m,[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+              entry->tag, exif_tag_get_name [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->tag[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Compute total data size and check overflow *[0m[35m/[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    unit = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39munit == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    s = unit * entry->components;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->components && s [0m[35m/[0m[39m entry->components != unit[0m[1;39m)[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Determine data location and bounds-check *[0m[35m/[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms <= [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Inline data at offset+[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset > SIZE_MAX - [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m8[0m[39m + s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m + s > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            exif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                      [0m[32m"Inline tag data overruns buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%zu + %zu > %zu[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m,[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                      offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        data_offset = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* External pointer field at offset+[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m..offset+[0m[1;36m11[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset > SIZE_MAX - [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m || offset + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            exif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                      [0m[32m"Cannot read data-offset field [0m[32m([0m[32m%zu + 12 > %zu[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m,[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                      offset, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        data_offset = exif_get_long [0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Ensure data block [0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdata_offset, data_offset+s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m fits *[0m[35m/[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata_offset > SIZE_MAX - s || data_offset + s > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        exif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                  [0m[32m"Tag data overruns buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%zu + %zu > %zu[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m,[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                  data_offset, s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Allocate and copy data *[0m[35m/[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    entry->data = exif_data_alloc [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned int[0m[1;39m)[0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!entry->data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[1;35mEXIF_LOG_NO_MEMORY[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    entry->size = [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned int[0m[1;39m)[0m[39ms;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    memcpy [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + data_offset, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* If this is the MakerNote, preserve its offset *[0m[35m/[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->tag == EXIF_TAG_MAKER_NOTE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpwo0dckjr[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer run on the `exif_from_data_fuzzer` harness uncovered a [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow in the function `exif_data_load_data_entry` within [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`libexif/exif-data.c`. The root crash was a multi-byte read past the end of a heap [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation during a `memcpy` of EXIF tag data. [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn attempted patch rewrote `exif_data_load_data_entry`, switching from `unsigned [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mint` to `size_t`, adding explicit header‐size checks, guarding against integer [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow in the size computation, and separating inline vs. external data cases [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith offset bounds checks. After rebuilding with the patch, the same [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer error reoccurs at the new `memcpy`, indicating the overflow is [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstill possible under certain inputs.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Running the fuzzer with a single testcase triggers an AddressSanitizer [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow in `exif_data_load_data_entry`.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The trace shows `__asan_memcpy` reading [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes at an address immediately [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpast a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m‐byte allocation.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Call stack:  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * `exif_data_load_data_entry` → `exif_data_load_data_content` → [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data` → `exif_data_new_from_data` → `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` → [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibFuzzer internals.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The faulty allocation size [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the subsequent read indicate that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomputed data length or offset checks were insufficient.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Function signature changed from  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `static int [0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_entry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mExifData *data, ExifEntry *entry, const [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munsigned char *d, unsigned int size, unsigned int offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     to  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `static int [0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_entry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mExifData *data, ExifEntry *entry, const [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munsigned char *d, size_t size, size_t offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added checks:  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Ensure at least [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m bytes remain at `offset` for the IFD entry header.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Compute `unit = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mformat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `s = unit * components` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith a multiplication‐overflow guard.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • If `s <= [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`, treat data as inline, verifying `offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m + s <= size`.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Otherwise read the external-data offset word at `offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`, then verify [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doff + s <= size`.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • On allocation failure, log and return.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch replaced older ad hoc checks [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`if doff >= size`, `if s > size - [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoff`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with the above structured conditions.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After applying the patch, the same fuzzer run reproduces a [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow in the revised `exif_data_load_data_entry` at the [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnow at line [0m[1;36m231[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The ASan log is nearly identical, showing a read [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes past a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregion.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Further Investigation Areas  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   To fully understand and resolve the overflow, the following code regions and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic should be reviewed:  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **IFD Entry Loop & Count Validation**  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * How many entries are declared and how is the loop bounded in [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_content`?  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Are there checks on the directory count or validation of the jump to [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`next_ifd_offset`?  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Integer Overflow and Type Ranges**  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Ensure that all arithmetic on `offset`, `size`, `components`, and `unit` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcannot overflow or wrap.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Confirm that `exif_format_get_size` never returns an unexpectedly large [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalue.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Allocation Size vs. Source Buffer**  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Verify `[0m[1;35mexif_data_alloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` always receives the correct bounds.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Check that the returned memory is fully addressable for `s` bytes.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Endian & Alignment Handling**  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * The code reads [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m- and [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte values via `exif_get_short` and [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_get_long`. Are there cases where `order` causes misinterpretation of offset [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfields?  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **External vs. Inline Data Semantics**  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * In the inline case [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s <= [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the code reads from `offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`. Does the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIFD specification guarantee that inline data always resides within those [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes?  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * In the external case, ensure that invalid offsets [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpointing before the IFD [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor overlapping it[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are caught.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA holistic audit of the IFD parsing and entry‐loading logic is needed to locate any[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremaining gap in boundary enforcement and to prevent reads or writes beyond the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mavailable buffer.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:    [0m[39m * has not been set yet[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:    [0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m177[0m[39m:    [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m178[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"Loading entry 0x%x [0m[32m([0m[32m'%s'[0m[32m)[0m[32m..."[0m[39m, entry->tag,[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m179[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m  exif_tag_get_name [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->tag[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m180[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m181[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* [0m[1;39m{[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m4[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m x [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0x00000000[0m[39m .. [0m[1;36m0xffffffff[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m182[0m[39m:    [0m[39m *   -> [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0x000000000[0m[39m .. [0m[1;36m0x7fffffff8[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:    [0m[39ms = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m * entry->components;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39ms < entry->components[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m{[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m187[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m188[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m*[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m189[0m[39m:    [0m[39m * Size? If bigger than [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes, the actual data is not[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m190[0m[39m:    [0m[39m * in the entry but somewhere else [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m191[0m[39m:    [0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m192[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m193[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mdoff = exif_get_long [0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibexif/exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:197[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m206[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m197[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Sanity checks *[0m[35m/[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m198[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m199[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m200[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"Tag starts past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, doff, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m201[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m202[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m203[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m204[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m205[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m206[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"Tag data goes past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoff+s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibexif/exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:424[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m442[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m424[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m425[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Read the number of entries *[0m[35m/[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m426[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset, ds, [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m427[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m428[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"Tag data past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u+2 > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, offset, ds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m429[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m430[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m431[0m[39m:    [0m[39mn = exif_get_short [0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m432[0m[39m:    [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m433[0m[39m:    [0m[39m          [0m[32m"Loading %hu entries..."[0m[39m, n[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m434[0m[39m:    [0m[39moffset += [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m435[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m436[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Check if we have enough data. *[0m[35m/[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m437[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset, ds, [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m*n[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m438[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mn = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mds - offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m439[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m440[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"Short data; only loading %hu entries..."[0m[39m, n[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m441[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m442[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Strengthen and unify all boundary checks in `exif_data_load_data_entry` to [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meliminate subtle off‐by one gaps, rather than piecemeal “> size” or “size – doff < [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ms” tests. In particular, replace the separate inline/external checks with a single [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Verify the [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m‐byte entry header fits in the buffer:[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Replace[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset > size || size - offset < [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        with[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. After computing the total data length `s` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwith overflow guard and `s > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, decide inline vs. external:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      size_t data_offset;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms <= [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          data_offset = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m ensure the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m‐byte pointer field is in‐bounds[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          data_offset = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Finally, unify the data‐copy guard as one simple check:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m ensure data_offset + s <= size[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size || data_offset > size - s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      This single comparison prevents reads at or beyond the end of the [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer—covering both doff > size and doff == size cases correctly.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Audit the IFD directory loop in `exif_data_load_data_content`:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Although `[0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset, ds, [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m*n[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` clamps the reported number of [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentries, it is safer to guard each iteration:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < n; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m > ds[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             break;                        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m no more full headers[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_entry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, entry, d, ds, offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         offset += [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This per‐entry header check prevents `exif_data_load_data_entry` from ever [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreceiving an `offset` that points past the [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m‐byte boundary.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Preserve all existing logic:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep the overflow‐safe multiplication for `s = unit * components`.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Continue using `[0m[1;35mexif_data_alloc[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` for the actual copy.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Retain the MakerNote special‐case logging and offset tracking.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Avoid broad exception or error catches. Only return early on failed bounds or [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation. Do not modify harness/tests or external dependencies.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Rationale and side‐effect mitigation:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By unifying the “data_offset + s <= size” check, we eliminate any scenario [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhere `doff == size` or arithmetic wrap can slip through, fixing the [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer‐observed [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m‐byte overflow start.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The revised header guard [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`offset + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m > size`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m simplifies and hardens [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry‐header validation.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Per‐entry loop guards in `exif_data_load_data_content` ensure that malformed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory counts cannot drive out‐of‐bounds `offset` values into the entry loader.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All other EXIF semantics and logging are untouched, minimizing risk to [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting downstream consumers.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Casting `s` to `unsigned int` for `exif_data_alloc` remains safe for typical [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEXIF sizes; extremely large components will be caught by the `s > size` or [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmultiplication‐overflow checks.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis comprehensive approach addresses the root‐cause boundary‐checking gaps, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrestores full ASan safety under fuzzing, and retains original functionality. [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m1[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/user/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mlibexif[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpwo0dckjr[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer run of `exif_from_data_fuzzer` uncovered a heap-buffer-overflow in [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` when processing certain malformed EXIF entries. The [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginal function computed entry sizes and offsets but did not fully guard against [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalformed or out-of-bounds offsets before calling `memcpy`. An attempt was made to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrewrite the entry loader to use `size_t` for bounds checks, guard against header [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand data overruns, and verify multiplication overflow. After applying this patch, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe fuzzer still crashes—now with a null-pointer dereference [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSEGV[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` at the newly inserted checks.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– The fuzzer invocation of `exif_from_data_fuzzer` triggered AddressSanitizer [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreporting a heap-buffer-overflow in  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  `exif_data_load_data_entry` at libexif’s `exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m[39m`.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Backtrace shows `__asan_memcpy` reading [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes past the end of a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation. The code path is:  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  exif_data_load_data_entry → exif_data_load_data_content → exif_data_load_data → [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_data_new_from_data → …  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– The offending read was due to insufficient checks on the computed data offset [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`doff`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and size [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m relative to the total buffer length. Although there were [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks for `doff >= size` and `s > size-doff`, they did not prevent certain [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmulti-byte reads [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. accessing the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset field or header[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverrunning the buffer.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– The patch rewrote `exif_data_load_data_entry` to:  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Treat `size` and `offset` as `size_t` and pre-check that a [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m-byte directory [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry header fits before reading any fields.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Read `tag`, `format`, and `components` only after this guard.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Compute `unit = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mformat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `s = unit*components`, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecking for zero, overflow, and that `s` fits within the buffer.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Differentiate inline data [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s ≤ [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from external data [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, each with its[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mown overrun checks.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Only then allocate and `memcpy` the data.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Added a guard in the containing loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_data_load_data_content`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to break [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout if fewer than [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m bytes remain for the next entry.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mResult after patch  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Running the same test corpus now produces a segmentation fault [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnull-dereference[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the patched `exif_data_load_data_entry` at line [0m[1;36m178[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39minside the initial [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheader-overrun check[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The crash log shows:  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    ERROR: AddressSanitizer: SEGV on unknown address [0m[1;36m0x2[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mWRITE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m exif_data_load_data_entry [0m[35m/src/libexif/libexif/[0m[95mexif-data.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m178:23[0m[39m  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m exif_data_load_data_content …  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– This indicates that one of the newly introduced pointer or index checks is either[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdereferencing a null or invalid pointer, or using an uninitialized `ExifEntry [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m*entry` in the call.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for further investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– The initialization and validity of `entry` passed into [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`. Is `entry` ever null or out of bounds?  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– The loop in `exif_data_load_data_content`: how many entries are allocated, and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhow is `entry` advanced or indexed? Ensure the loop’s index `i` and pointer [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marithmetic align with the actual array size.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– The header-guard logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`if [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset > SIZE_MAX - [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m || offset + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubsequent use of `d + offset`. A miscomputed offset or use of `SIZE_MAX` could [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallow `offset` to wrap or become negative when converted, leading to a tiny pointer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand the null-page deref.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Consistency between inline-data branch and external-data branch: both guard [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`offset + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m`, but the second branch repeats the same check rather than guarding [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte read at `d + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m` in isolation.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m– Any wider context in `exif_data_load_data_content` or `exif_data_load_data` that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomputes `ds`, `n`, or `offset` and passes them down. Boundary conditions there may[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe contributing to `offset` being invalid at the patched function entry.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo assumptions have been made about root causes beyond what is observable in the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogs. Further code review and targeted tests around zero-length inputs, extreme [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponent counts, and malformed header offsets will be needed to locate the precise[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnull-pointer use.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
